[2026-03-27 19:58:12] DOMAIN-ENRICHED TRAINING EXPERIMENT
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] ======================================================================
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] INSIGHT: Previous experiments used generic C4 where >80% of tokens
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] are general text. Experts can't specialize on homogeneous data.
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] 
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] SOLUTION: Hard-filter C4 for domain purity. Each batch is 100%
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] one domain. Domain-conditional gradient masking ensures each
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] specialist expert only learns from its domain.
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] 
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] ARCHITECTURE: DeepSeek shared+routed design:
[2026-03-27 19:58:12]   Expert 0 (code): learns from code batches only
[2026-03-27 19:58:12]   Expert 1 (medical): learns from medical batches only
[2026-03-27 19:58:12]   Expert 2 (shared): learns from ALL batches
[2026-03-27 19:58:12]   Router picks between code/medical; shared always active.
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] 
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] SUCCESS: M_ij diagonal dominance > 0.3
[2026-03-27 19:58:12] FAILURE: One expert absorbs everything (capacity issue at rank-4)
